---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Survival Guide"
  description="Part II: The Survival Guide — practical strategies for alienated parents in the acute phase. Legal options, communication, and protecting your mental health."
>
  <section class="section section-dark hub-hero">
    <div class="container-narrow" style="text-align:center;">
      <p class="part-label">Part II</p>
      <h1>The Survival Guide</h1>
      <p class="hub-intro">
        Practical strategies for the acute phase: legal options, communication tactics,
        and how to protect your mental health when everything is falling apart.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container-narrow prose">
      <p>
        When you are in the middle of parental alienation — the legal battles, the silence
        from your child, the sense of powerlessness — what you need most is not theory.
        You need things you can actually do.
      </p>
      <p>
        Articles in this section are practical and specific: what legal options exist and
        how realistic they are, how to communicate with your child in ways that preserve
        the relationship, how to manage your mental health under sustained stress, and
        how to avoid the mistakes that make things worse.
      </p>
      <p style="color:var(--color-warm-grey); font-style:italic;">
        Articles coming soon. Download the free Survival Guide for immediate practical help.
      </p>
      <a href="/free-guide" class="btn btn-primary" style="margin-top:1rem;">
        Get the Free Survival Guide →
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
.hub-hero { padding-block: 6rem; }
.part-label {
  font-size: 0.78rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: 0.12em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--color-amber-light);
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}
.hub-intro {
  font-size: 1.1rem;
  color: rgba(247,243,238,0.8);
  margin-top: 1.25rem;
  line-height: 1.75;
}
</style>
